Jorge Simao was appointed coach of Portuguese top flight side Sporting Braga on Saturday, after predecessor Jose Peseiro was sacked following the club&#8217;s Europa League exit.Portugal&#8217;s Simao, 40, had coached top flight side Chaves until last May, after previously leading teams such as Pacos Ferreira and Belenenses.Braga, currently fourth in the league, sacked 56-year-old Peseiro after the team were eliminated from the Portuguese Cup and Europa League.-AFP